entry.title: Fix RFHI::pending_navigate_ cleanup after crashes and early RFH swaps.
entry.content:
When resuming a navigation that had been saved into

RenderFrameHostImpl::pending_navigate_, we need to account for the

fact that OnBeginNavigation() calls GetFrameHostForNavigation() which

may perform an early RenderFrameHost swap and synchronously destroy

the old RFH.



There's also no need to keep a pending_navigate_ around after the

corresponding renderer process crashes, so this CL also adds logic to

clear it. Resuming such a navigation would require additional work,

since the NavigationClient stashed in pending_navigate_ is no longer

usable and would just immediately call the disconnect handler and

cancel the navigation. But there isn't really any benefit to adding

that complexity, and we already cancel the RFH's other ongoing

navigations when its renderer process dies.



This CL also tweaks the logic in RenderWidgetHostImpl to allow the

resuming logic (ResumeLoadingCreatedWebContents) to work without

hitting DCHECKs, if it's called after a renderer process crash. This

case never worked cleanly before, but is supported now (and allows the

new test to work without crashing).

entry.title: [EditContext] Don't set WebTextInputInfo composition ranges if no composition
entry.content:
WebTextInputInfo [1] has a convention where

composition_start/composition_end are set to -1 to indicate there is

no composition. EditContext has a separate bool to track

has_composition_, and keeps composition_range_start_/end_ at 0 when

there is no composition.



EditContext's convention was getting applied to WebTextInputInfo,

erroneously indicating that a composition open when there was not.

This was causing issues with Android touch keyboard suggestions:

when the user chooses a suggested word, the same set of suggestions

are displayed again rather than advancing to the next suggested

word in the sentence.



Fix the issue by leaving WebTextInputInfo.composition_start/

composition_end at -1 if EditContext has no composition.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/public/platform/web_text_input_info.h

entry.title: Implement an unprefixed mask-image property
entry.content:
This patch adds an updated and unprefixed mask-image property behind

the experimental flag CSSMaskingInterop. A new test has been added for

cases with both mask-image and -webkit-mask-image, which is important

for web compatibility. Test expectations have been updated for the

newly-passing tests. In addition to unprefixing, the patch removes

support (also behind the flag) for the non-standard cross-fade

interpolation of mask-images, which now matches both WebKit and Gecko.



The implementation approach in css_properties.json5 is novel, and is

based on a prototype by andruud@chromium.org. The approach is to add

a new flag-guarded property, "mask-image", which is a copy of the

existing "-webkit-mask-image" property. Then, a new flag-guarded

alternative of "-webkit-mask-image" is added, which is an alias of the

"mask-image" property ("-webkit-alternative-mask-image"). This ensures

that "-webkit-mask-image" uses the new "mask-image" code when the flag

is enabled. To ensure the "-webkit-mask" shorthand property uses the new

"mask-image" property, a flag-guarded alternative of "-webkit-mask" is

also added.



To remove support for interpolation, the new "mask-image" property does

not have "interpolable: true".



Bug: 432153

entry.title: arc/tracing: get smaller trace JSON to avoid ooms
entry.content:
Before this CL we were subscribed to all viz events, which generated

roughly 50MB JSON as the raw trace results for 2 minute traces. This

could not be parsed on 4GB ChromeOS devices, and 20 minute traces could

not be parsed on 8GB devices. The JSON parser would run out of memory

and the Chrome process would crash.



In the trace config, register for only one category which generates only

a single event, which is the one we care about (vsync with new frame).

This allows 4GB devices to handle the JSON for 20 minute traces. The raw

JSON output of a 2 minute trace is reduced to about 160KiB.



Remove event matchers from the mapper for other viz events which we can

no longer receive and which arc-overview-tracing does not support.



Test: Trace an app window for 1200 seconds on a 4GB RAM nautilus

Bug: b/302382849
